We are seeking an entry level AI Engineer with a strong interest in Generative AI (GenAI), Agentic AI, and Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG).


In this role, you will work alongside senior engineers and data scientists to build, test, and deploy AI powered applications using Large Language Models (LLMs), vector databases, and agent frameworks.


This position is ideal for early career engineers who are strong in Python and software fundamentals and are eager to build production ready GenAI solutions, not just experiments.


Primary Responsibilities:

Generative AI & LLM Development
Assist in designing and developing GenAI based applications using Large Language Models (LLMs)
Implement prompt engineering, prompt chaining, and basic fine tuning techniques under guidance
Evaluate LLM outputs for quality, safety, hallucination risks, and performance
RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation)
Build and maintain RAG pipelines by integrating LLMs with document stores and vector databases
Assist in data ingestion, chunking strategies, embedding generation, and retrieval evaluation
Work on use cases such as chat with documents, enterprise search, and knowledge assistants
Agentic AI
Contribute to the development of AI agents capable of tool use, multi step reasoning, and workflow orchestration
Implement simple autonomous or semi autonomous agents using agent frameworks under supervision
Help define agent goals, constraints, and guardrails
Software Engineering & Integration
Develop backend services and APIs (REST / FastAPI) to expose AI capabilities to applications
Write clean, testable Python code following software engineering best practices
Participate in code reviews, testing, and debugging of AI systems
Data & Model Operations
Assist with data preparation for structured and unstructured datasets
Support experimentation, benchmarking, and comparison of GenAI approaches
Follow responsible AI practices, including secure handling of sensitive data (PII/PHI)
What You Will Learn
Building production grade GenAI systems, not just demos
Designing agent based workflows for real business use cases
Applying RAG patterns to enterprise knowledge and documents
Working within an AI first software development lifecycle
Best practices for safe, reliable, and scalable AI solutions
